<p>Use the strategy of the decimal to binary conversion implemented in Project 4.4, and the bit shift left operation defined in Project 4.5 to code a new encryption algorithm.</p>

<p>The algorithm should</p>

<ul>
  <li>Add 1 to each characterâ€™s numeric ASCII value.</li>
  <li>Convert it to a bit string.</li>
  <li>Shift the bits of this string one place to the left.</li>
</ul>

<p>A single-space character in the encrypted string separates the resulting bit strings.</p>

<p>An example of the program input and output is shown below:</p>

<div class="language-text highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Enter a message: Hello world!

0010011 1001101 1011011 1011011 1100001 000011 1110001 1100001 1100111 1011011 1001011 000101
</code></pre></div></div>

